        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2017-10-06 19:27:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nI think this patch is fine, but not necessary. All the calls to 'quote_error p' (note: quote_error calls quota_scan) send $TSTPRJID as the second argument (local_id). With this patch, you're just enforcing that the correct local_id is being used.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "ac5f8ff61cf02b9a88887c86019b2633a015546c",
      "author": {
